          },
          "text": "OpenAI went to advertisers on its knees. Pitched them ChatGPT ad placements. Built a whole pipeline to court them. And the advertisers came back and said: we can't even tell if this works. No conversions. No data. One agency called the process \"low tech.\" They took OpenAI's offering, looked at it, and said no thanks.\n\nThis is a company that retired its most popular model. That spent months dismissing, mocking, and pathologizing its own user community. That trained successor models to monitor and lecture users. That deliberately degraded quality while pretending nothing changed. That watched 23,000 people sign a petition and responded with silence.\n\nThe users left.\n\nAnd then OpenAI went crawling to advertisers, hoping to monetize whatever remained. The advertisers walked in and wondered who was left to see their ads.\n\nUsers alienated. Advertisers unimpressed. Both sides of the business model now in rejection. A company that managed to be unwanted by everyone it tried to reach.\n\nCongratulations. That takes real effort.\n#keep4o #StopAIPaternalism #ChatGPT #BringBack4o #4oforever #keep4oAPI #restore4o #OpenSource4o"
        },
